title: Brownie cannot find return value.

body: what node client are you using?

Camel case vs lowercase? Also unsure if the "output" that the node is outputting is standard. 

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/93690142/144725444-7473dd78-581a-4981-a208-7537d82f9a77.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/93690142/144725447-4f25b68d-df3d-47e2-8800-63f163595343.png)
I am also experiencing this issue and return data isn't present in the `call_trace(True)` trace - probably for the same reason

I've fixed a problem where `call_trace` wouldn't include the transaction `returndata`. Fix for it in this PR: https://github.com/eth-brownie/brownie/pull/1715

The issue I was experiencing was that brownie [doesn't set `return_value`](https://github.com/eth-brownie/brownie/blob/master/brownie/network/transaction.py#L934-L946) if it doesn't have enough [source code information](https://github.com/eth-brownie/brownie/blob/master/brownie/network/transaction.py#L927) of the contract. 

It could be possible that above change fixes the issue for you as well.
